# 13 May 2013 - Uniform Peaks of Transcription Factor ChIP-seq from ENCODE/Analysis. UCSC has released a new browser track containing 690 datasets of transcription factor ChIP-seq peaks based on data from all five ENCODE TFBS ChIP-seq production groups from the project inception in 2007 through the ENCODE March 2012 data freeze. The track covers 161 unique regulatory factors (generic and sequence-specific factors), spanning 91 human cell types, some under various treatment conditions.
lftp -c mirror http://hgdownload.cse.ucsc.edu/goldenPath/hg19/encodeDCC/wgEncodeAwgTfbsUniform/
